---
import LegalLayout from '../layouts/LegalLayout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../lib/site';
---

<LegalLayout title="Affiliate Disclosure" description="How TrailNestCo uses affiliate links and how that relates to our editorial recommendations." path="/affiliate-disclosure" updated="June 1, 2026">
  <p>
    In accordance with the FTC's Guides Concerning the Use of Endorsements and Testimonials, {SITE.name}
    discloses the following: this website contains affiliate links. If you click one of these links and
    make a purchase, {SITE.business.legalName} may receive a commission from the retailer or affiliate
    network, at no additional cost to you.
  </p>

  <h2>Which networks we work with</h2>
  <p>
    {SITE.name} participates in affiliate programs through networks including Awin, Impact, and CJ
    Affiliate, as well as individual retailer affiliate programs. The specific program backing any given
    link may change over time as we add or rotate partners.
  </p>

  <h2>How this affects our content</h2>
  <p>
    Affiliate relationships do not influence which products we choose to test, how we score them, or where
    they rank in our guides. Our editorial team builds rankings and recommendations before affiliate links
    are added to a page, following the process described in our <a href="/editorial-policy">Editorial
    Policy</a>. We link to a product because we believe it's a good fit for the use case described —
    if a non-affiliate retailer is the best source for a product, we'll link there too.
  </p>

  <h2>Identifying affiliate links</h2>
  <p>
    Buttons such as "Check price," "Visit official site," and "Try free version" are typically affiliate
    links. Every article that contains affiliate links also displays a short disclosure notice near the
    top or bottom of the page.
  </p>

  <h2>Questions</h2>
  <p>
    If you have questions about a specific link or our affiliate relationships, contact us at
    <a href={`mailto:${SITE.business.contactEmail}`}>{SITE.business.contactEmail}</a>.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
